                <tr><td><strong>Debt Funds</strong></td><td>Low</td><td>6%–8%</td><td>1–3 years</td><td>Capital preservation</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Hybrid Funds</strong></td><td>Moderate</td><td>10%–13%</td><td>3–5 years</td><td>Balanced risk-return</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Returns are historical averages and not guaranteed. Past performance does not indicate future results. Data as of March 2026.</em></p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Invest in Mutual Funds?</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Professional Fund Management</strong><p>Your money is managed by experienced fund managers backed by dedicated research teams. They analyze markets, select securities, and rebalance portfolios — saving you the time and expertise needed for direct stock or bond investing.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Diversification Across Securities</strong><p>A single mutual fund invests in 30–80 different securities, spreading risk across companies, sectors, and asset classes. This diversification significantly reduces the impact of any single stock's poor performance on your portfolio.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>SIP: Invest Small, Build Big</strong><p>Systematic Investment Plans allow you to invest as little as ₹500 per month. SIPs leverage rupee cost averaging — buying more units when markets are low and fewer when high — delivering superior long-term returns.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Tax Efficiency</strong><p>ELSS funds offer Section 80C deduction up to ₹1.5 lakh. Equity fund gains held over 1 year are taxed at only 12.5% (LTCG above ₹1.25 lakh). Debt funds held over 3 years benefit from indexation on capital gains.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>High Liquidity</strong><p>Open-ended mutual funds can be redeemed on any business day at the prevailing NAV. Redemption proceeds are typically credited within 1–3 business days, providing excellent liquidity compared to FDs or bonds.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Complete Transparency & Regulation</strong><p>SEBI mandates daily NAV disclosure, monthly portfolio holdings, and standardized risk categorization. All fees and charges are clearly disclosed, and fund performance data is publicly available for informed decision-making.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How to Invest</span><h2>How to Start Investing in Mutual Funds</h2></div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Complete KYC</h3><p>One-time KYC verification with PAN, Aadhaar, and bank details. Complete e-KYC online in 5 minutes through any AMC website, registrar (CAMS/KFintech), or our platform.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Choose Fund Category</h3><p>Select based on your goals: large cap for stability, mid/small cap for growth, ELSS for tax saving, or debt funds for capital preservation. Our advisors can recommend the right mix.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Start SIP or Lump Sum</h3><p>Set up a SIP for regular monthly investing (₹500 minimum) or invest a lump sum. SIP auto-debits from your bank account on a chosen date each month for hassle-free investing.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Monitor & Rebalance</h3><p>Track your portfolio performance through our dashboard. Review annually and rebalance if your asset allocation drifts from your target. Stay invested for the long term to maximize compounding benefits.</p></div>
            </div>
